<p>I am trying to build an android app that gets the auth token from GoogleAuthUtil getToken method.The scope I am using: </p>  <pre><code>String SCOPE = "oauth2:https://www.googleapis.com/auth/userinfo.profile"; </code></pre>  <p>I am successully getting the token but when I test the token with a few different email address:</p>  <pre><code>https://www.googleapis.com/oauth2/v1/tokeninfo?access_token=&lt;token&gt; </code></pre>  <p>I only get email in json response for some emails while for rest I don't get the email address. I get two different responses . </p>  <p>Without email:</p>  <pre><code>{  "issued_to": "",  "audience": "",  "user_id": "",  "scope": "https://www.googleapis.com/auth/userinfo.profile",  "expires_in": 3587,  "access_type": "online" } </code></pre>  <p>With email:</p>  <pre><code>{  "issued_to": "",  "audience": "",  "user_id": "",  "scope": "https://www.googleapis.com/auth/userinfo.profile https://www.googleapis.com/auth/userinfo.email",  "expires_in": 3444,  "email": "",  "verified_email": true,  "access_type": "online" } </code></pre>  <p>Inside django views.py :</p>  <pre><code>@psa('social:complete') def register_by_token(request, backend):     token = request.GET.get('access_token')     user = request.backend.do_auth(request.GET.get('access_token'))     if user:         login(request, user)         return HttpResponse("Successfully logged in")     else:         return HttpResponse("Error Logging In") </code></pre>  <p>When I pass the token (with email) the user is created but not in the other case.</p>  <p>Please suggest what to do.I am unable to understand why the GoogleAuthUtil is generating two different tokens with different scopes while I have single scope defined. I am new to oauth so please let me know if I need to share any other details.</p>